description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using version 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}
2. Compile the class using the following command: ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory.

Expected Behavior:
The behavior should be the same as javac.

Steps to Reproduce:
Include the -d option while correctly compiling classes from a subpackage.
